{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778338112,"nonce":"zyhv7RvdA+l+zZYVhQRHO+882HQ=","message":"**Updates to consider when this run happens** (since this issue was filed):\n\n- New task structure on rlrmp main: `epoch_len_ranges = [[0, 1], [10, 30]]` — pure-hold collapsed, target-on bumped to 100-300 ms (Shahbazi 2025 §4.2 alignment). Should be the default for any vRNN τ-sweep.\n- Output-jerk loss `nn_output_jerk = 1e5` is now available (issue `7e1d257`, merged via `89e9a85c`). Strongly recommend including in vRNN runs — was the primary variance-reduction lever in the prior 2x2x2 GRU matrix.\n- Hidden-state smoothness loss `nn_hidden_derivative` (issue `e8f3738`, merged via `0fcbd9d1`) is also available. Mostly relevant if combined with `tau` sweep — different time-constants may interact with smoothness penalty differently.\n- Open question: the prior 2x2x2 baseline matrix (efc4d68 comment `ecfecc4`) showed vRNN under-converges at 12k batches with α=1.0. Some of that may be rescued by α=0.1 (the new default) plus the longer 100-300 ms target-on window; the τ-sweep on top of that is the real follow-up. Recommend baseline τ ∈ {0.02, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.5} with all the above loss-side defaults active.\n\nCross-refs: `5acdaae` (anti-anticipation), `efc4d68` (smoothness umbrella), `2bc95fd` (3-cell pre-reg with task structure change).","files":null}]}